The '''tit berrypecker''' ('''''Oreocharis arfaki''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Paramythiidae]]. First described by [[Christian Erich Hermann von Meyer]] in 1875, it is [[monotypic]] within the genus '''''Oreocharis'''''.<ref name = "ITIS"/> It is found in the [[New Guinea Highlands]] and more scarcely in northern parts of the island, in subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />

